HEADWORD: Ecbasis
<hw>Ec"ba*sis</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧k"b⟦adot⟧*s⟦icr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L., fr. Gr. <grk>'e`kbasis</grk> a going out, issue, or event;
<grk>'ek</grk> out + <grk>bai`nein</grk> to go.]</ety>
<fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>A figure in which the orator treats of things
according to their events consequences.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

